result.execSummary:
The defendant Jared Allen Gora was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Disorderly Conduct [Modifiers: Domestic Abuse], a class B misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 947.01(1).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

supervisions.notes: Defendant eligible for huber for work.  Defendant eligible for electronic monitoring.

Restitution ordered: $650 - M.P.; $65 - surcharge.  Bond money to be applied to restutition.  Balance to be paid at the rate of $100 per month beginning 03/01/16 and on the first of each subsequent month until paid in full.    If not paid, one day in jail for each $40.00 of unpaid fines.
To be paid with payment plan as stated in Restitution.    If not paid, one day in jail for each $40.00 of unpaid fines.
